SUMMARY:Health disparities in America: Why the innovation community needs 
 to be a part of the solution
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260414T180000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260414T190000
DTSTAMP:20260419T063624Z
UID:6d92439c075341d3@gid-seminars.wnprc.wisc.edu
CATEGORIES:Lecture/Presentation/Talk
DESCRIPTION:Speaker: Stella Safo\, MD\, MPH\nFounder and CEO at Just Equit
 y for Health\nMaintaining an equity lens in health innovation during turbu
 lent times requires both vision and practical strategy.\n\nIn this talk\, 
 Stella Safo -an HIV primary care physician\, public health practitioner\, 
 and passionate advocate-will discuss the health disparities present in Ame
 rica and will draw on real-world examples\, like the 'Green Book for Healt
 h'\, to explore how community-centered healthcare solutions can meaningful
 ly build stronger\, healthier communities.\n\nWhether you're an entreprene
 ur\, healthcare provider\, policymaker\, community organizer\, or someone 
 invested in health justice\, this discussion will equip you with tools to 
 advance equitable care.\n\nEvent URL: https://events.stanford.edu/event/he
 alth-disparities-in-america-why-the-innovation-community-needs-to-be-a-par
 t-of-the-solution\n\nSource: stanford_virtual
LOCATION:Online
