DESCRIPTION:[Podcast: This Week in Virology]\n\nTWiV explains a study show
 ing that the wildlife trade\, including live-animal markets\, is a major d
 river of animal-to-human pathogen transmission\, and ecological vaccinatio
 n\, a strategy to prevent zoonotic spillover from bats. Hosts: Vincent Rac
 aniello \, Alan Dove \, Rich Condit \, and Angela Mingarelli Click arrow t
 o play Download TWiV 1315 (66 MB .mp3\, 110 min) Subscribe (free): Apple P
 odcasts \, RSS \, email Become a&nbsp\; patron &nbsp\;of&nbsp\;TWiV! Links
  for this episode Support science education at MicrobeTV Positions in Rose
 nfeld Lab (email) Bernard Roizman passes ( Wikipedia ) Maturation of a sci
 entist (Ann Rev Virology) Wildlife trade drives pathogen transmission (Sci
 ence) Ecological vaccination of bats (Sci Adv) Letters read &nbsp\; on TWi
 V 1315 Timestamps by&nbsp\; Jolene Ramsey. Thanks! Weekly Picks Angela &#8
 211\; Real-time tracking of pathogen evolution Rich &#8211\; A Precarious 
 Perch \; Suwannee’s track \; Avian Research and Conservation Institute A
 lan &#8211\; Bookshop.org Vincent &#8211\; The Mysterious 30 Year Journey 
 of Apollo 12 Listener Picks Fernando &#8211\; Sean M. Carroll&#8217\;s ser
 ies &#8220\;The Biggest Ideas in the Universe&#8221\;: &#8220\;Space\, Tim
 e\, and Motion&#8221\;\, and &#8220\;Quanta and Fields .&#8221\; Intro mus
 ic is by&nbsp\; Ronald Jenkees Send your virology questions and comments t
 o twiv@microbe.tv Content in this podcast should not be construed as medic
 al advice. The post TWiV 1315: Jabs for bats first appeared on This Week i
 n Virology .\n\nEvent URL: https://www.microbe.tv/twiv/twiv-1315/\n\nSourc
 e: twiv_podcast
