CATEGORIES:Fred Hutch Center for AIDS Research (CFAR)
DESCRIPTION:Event interval: Single day event\nCampus location: Hans Roslin
 g Center for Population Health (HRC)\nCampus room: 155\nAccessibility Cont
 act: dghcomm@uw.edu\nEvent Types: Lectures/Seminars\nEvent sponsors: This 
 Department of Global Health event is co-sponsored by the School&nbsp\;of P
 ublic Health\, the Department of Anthropology\, the Department of Law Soci
 eties and Justice\, the Center for AIDS Research (CFAR)\, the Center for A
 nti-Racism and Community Health (ARCH)\, the African Studies Program\, and
  the American Association of University Professors (AAUP). &nbsp\;\nLink: 
 https://bit.ly/4tArZHF\n\nPlease RSVP by Friday\, April 24: https://bit.ly
 /4tArZHF\n\nThe Seattle region is home to the third largest Somali‑Ameri
 can community in the nation\, and Somali‑American students\, staff\, and
  faculty have long been an integral part of the UW community. The UW Schoo
 l of Public Health has a long history of training and collaboration with S
 omali-American health professionals to build impactful partnerships. Join 
 us for a dynamic panel featuring Somali‑American UW students\, faculty\,
  and alumni alongside UW faculty. They will highlight public health collab
 orations in our region and focus on how the UW can continue to support and
  stand in partnership with the Somali‑American community during this cri
 tical time. \n\nPanel Participants: \n	 - Ahmed Abdille - WSU Pharm.D. \, 
 former Somali Health Board (SHB) Executive Director and business leader 	\
 n - Najma Osman - UW MPH in Global Health\, current Executive Director of 
 SHB 	\n - Farah Mohamed - UW MPH in Global Health\, current DrGH student 	
 \n - Mohamed Ali - UW MPH in Global Health\, founder of SHB\, Environmenta
 l Health Planner\, King County Public Health 	\n - Sumaya Mohamed - UW MPH
  in Global Health\, current UW PhD student in Anthropology 	\n - Anisa Ibr
 ahim MD - UW MD\, UW Clinical Associate Professor of Pediatrics and Medica
 l Director\, Pediatric Clinic\, Harborview Medical Center\nModerators:\n	 
 - Rachel Chapman - UW Professor\, Anthropology 	\n - Keshet Ronen - \n\nEv
 ent URL: https://bit.ly/4tArZHF\n\nSource: uw_cfar
