BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Coincidence Analysis Workshop
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260507T160000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260507T230000
DTSTAMP:20260419T063624Z
UID:0019af18d9fee1d7@gid-seminars.wnprc.wisc.edu
CATEGORIES:Fred Hutch Center for AIDS Research (CFAR)
DESCRIPTION:Event interval: Single day event\nCampus location: Hans Roslin
 g Center for Population Health (HRC)\nCampus room: HRC 101\nAccessibility 
 Contact: emm234@uw.edu\nEvent Types: Workshops\nEvent sponsors: CFAR Imple
 mentation Science Core and Data Sciences and Methods Core\n\nRegister Here
 : \nhttps://forms.office.com/pages/responsepage.aspx?id=W9229i_wGkSZoBYqxQ
 YL0pb3J3CJc0lAoU6qHfbkyXFUMjVJM0FNQ0hUMTlBSk83ODFLM0hZV1dXTy4u&route=short
 url!\n \n-----------------------------------------------------------------
 ---------------\nJoin us for an in-person workshop on Coincidence Analysis
  (CNA)! \nCNA is a configurational comparative method\, which includes cas
 e-based approaches that identify combinations of conditions that are neces
 sary and/or sufficient for the presence or absence of a certain outcome. L
 earn how CNA can be used to understand how different patient characteristi
 cs are related to clinical symptoms or how different contextual factors co
 ntribute to the implementation of evidence-based practices.\n\nWorkshop Ag
 enda:\n	 - Morning Session (9am - 12pm): Intro to CNA	\n		 - CNA Purpose &
  Methods		\n - How to Write about CNA in Grants & Papers	\n		\n - Afternoo
 n Session (1pm - 4pm): Hands-on Practice! **	\n		 - Use provided data to p
 ractice running CNA in R/RStudio and ask in-depth questions about CNA (**a
 ttendance at the afternoon session is optional)	\n	\nWorkshop Facilitator:
  Clara Johnson\, MS\, Dept of Clinical Psychology \n\nClara Johnson is a 6
 th year PhD Student in Clinical Psychology at UW and uses CNA in much of h
 er implementation science research. She attended the 4-day CNA course in 2
 024\, co-taught the first graduate-level CNA course at the University of W
 ashington in Spring 2024\, and presented at the annual CNA conference in 2
 025.\n\nEvent URL: https://forms.office.com/pages/responsepage.aspx?id=W92
 29i_wGkSZoBYqxQYL0pb3J3CJc0lAoU6qHfbkyXFUMjVJM0FNQ0hUMTlBSk83ODFLM0hZV1dXT
 y4u&route=shorturl\n\nSource: uw_cfar
LOCATION:Hans Rosling Center for Population Health (HRC)
URL:https://forms.office.com/pages/responsepage.aspx?id=W9229i_wGkSZoBYqxQ
 YL0pb3J3CJc0lAoU6qHfbkyXFUMjVJM0FNQ0hUMTlBSk83ODFLM0hZV1dXTy4u&route=short
 url
BEGIN:VALARM
ACTION:DISPLAY
DESCRIPTION:Reminder: Coincidence Analysis Workshop
TRIGGER:-PT1H
END:VALARM
END:VEVENT
